<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5392971>
    dc:description "FIG. 17. — Nipponithyris lauensis n. sp., Fiji, Lau Ridge, BORDAU 1: A-C, dorsal, anterior and lateral views of complete specimen, paratype (MNHN BRA-3112), stn DW 1485, 700-707 m; D-G, ventral, dorsal, laterial and anterior views of complete specimen, holotype (MNHN BRA-3111), stn DW 1485, 700-707 m; H, I, posterior part of dorsal valve interior, and enlargement (I) to show details of connecting band and crural processes, paratype (MNHN BRA-3113), SEM, stn DW 1432, 477-493 m; J, K, dorsal and side views of interior of dorsal valve to show brachial loop, paratype (MNHN BRA-3114), SEM, stn DW 1408, 550-561 m; L, M, inner views of ventral valve, tilted (M) to show swollen bases and grooves to accommodate inner socket ridges, paratype (MNHN BRA-3115), SEM, stn DW 1432, 477-493 m. Scale bars: A-G, 0.5 cm; H, I, 1 mm; J-M, 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5392971/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

